A cyclops (plural cyclopes) is a large one-eyed monster. They are known for dropping many alchable drops, so bringing nature and fire runes is helpful as it allows players to make longer trips and more money without banking or taking up inventory space.

Cyclopes may be killed as a substitute for hill giants on a Slayer task.

Defenders[edit | edit source]

Main article: Defender

Cyclopes in the Warriors' Guild have a rare chance of dropping a defender. These defensive weapons range from bronze to dragon and must be obtained in order, starting with bronze, by killing cyclopes on the top floor of the Warriors' Guild and then showing the defender to Kamfreena outside the chamber. Once a player earns the rune defender, they can enter the basement of the Warriors' Guild and kill the stronger cyclopes found there for a chance at the dragon defender. As this is located in the Warriors' Guild, cyclopes found in these areas are immune to Ranged and Magic attacks and must be fought with melee combat.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
28 October 2020
(update)

The cyclopes in the Catacombs of Kourend are no longer immune to magic or ranged attacks.

8 August 2019
(update)

The drop rate for ecumenical keys have been changed to be 1/60 regardless of keys owned.

19 March 2015
(update)

The bonecrusher now crushes bones dropped by Cyclopes in the Warrior's guild basement.

5 February 2015
(update | poll)

Level 106 Cyclopes have been added to the Warriors' Guild basement; they have a chance of dropping dragon defenders.

29 March 2004
(update)

The NPC was permanently added with the launch of RuneScape 2.

2 February 2004
(update)

The NPC was released ingame to the RuneScape 2 Beta.

1 December 2003
(update)

The NPC was added to the RuneScape 2 Beta cache.
